1 NEW SECTION. SECTION 2. NOTIFICATION OF COUNTY SHERIFF. (1) A FEDERAL EMPLOYEE OR OTHER
2 AGENT OR INDIVIDUAL ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT WHO IS NOT DESIGNATED BY STATE LAW AS A
3 MONTANA PEACE OFFICER MAY NOT MAKE AN ARREST, SEARCH, OR SEIZURE IN THIS STATE WITHOUT PROVIDING NOTICE
4 OF THE ACTION TO THE SHERIFF OR A DESIGNEE OF THE SHERIFF OF THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE ARREST, SEARCH, OR
5 SEIZURE WILL OCCUR UNLESS:
6 (A) THE INTENDED SUBJECT OF THE ARREST, SEARCH, OR SEIZURE IS AN EMPLOYEE OF THE SHERIFF'S
7 OFFICE OR IS AN ELECTED COUNTY OR STATE OFFICER; OR
8 (B) THE FEDERAL EMPLOYEE OR OTHER AGENT OR INDIVIDUAL ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE FEDERAL
9 GOVERNMENT HAS PROBABLE CAUSE TO BELIEVE THAT THE SUBJECT OF THE ARREST, SEARCH, OR SEIZURE HAS CLOSE
10 CONNECTIONS WITH THE SHERIFF AND THAT THE CONNECTIONS ARE LIKELY TO RESULT IN THE SUBJECT BEING INFORMED
11 OF THE IMPENDING ARREST, SEARCH, OR SEIZURE.
12 (2) IF A FEDERAL EMPLOYEE OR OTHER AGENT OR INDIVIDUAL ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE FEDERAL
13 GOVERNMENT WHO IS NOT DESIGNATED BY STATE LAW AS A MONTANA PEACE OFFICER IS EXEMPT UNDER SUBSECTIONS
14 (1)(A) AND (1)(B) FROM PROVIDING NOTICE TO THE COUNTY SHERIFFS, THE FEDERAL EMPLOYEE OR OTHER AGENT OR
15 INDIVIDUAL ACTING ON BEHALF OF THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT SHALL PROVIDE NOTICE TO THE ATTORNEY GENERAL.
16
17 NEW SECTION. SECTION 3. CODIFICATION INSTRUCTION. [SECTIONS 1 AND 2] ARE INTENDED TO BE
18 CODIFIED AS AN INTEGRAL PART OF TITLE 44, AND THE PROVISIONS OF TITLE 44 APPLY TO [SECTIONS 1 AND 2].
19
20 NEW SECTION. SECTION 4. EFFECTIVE DATE. [THIS ACT] IS EFFECTIVE ON PASSAGE AND APPROVAL.
21 - END -
